          "Limitations"
        ],
        [
          "Higher Education",
          "E-Learning",
          "AI-driven remedial recommender / adaptive concept-based recommender using knowledge-gap identification, LLM-generated remedial content, and adaptive follow-up evaluation",
          "Weak knowledge concepts; recommendations include learning objectives, review topics, remedial explanation, practice activities, and concept-gap rationale",
          "262 learners for recommendation-module analysis",
          "Procedural Programming using C (evaluation setting); broader curriculum processing spans 70+ CSE courses",
          "Curriculum PDFs, OBE exam data from AMPLE LMS, learner-question performance, concept/outcome mappings, instructor-defined attainment rules",
          "Initialized from curriculum processing and concept extraction; instructor validates concepts and defines thresholds/targets and question rules; weak concepts are identified from learner performance",
          "Iterative closed loop: after studying recommendations, learners complete self-assessment; results are fed back and the system generates refined recommendations until target mastery is reached",
          "PDF-to-text conversion, RAG-based retrieval, embeddings/vector DB, semantic deduplication for follow-up questions, multi-model cross-verification of generated remedial content",
          "Personalized remedial recommendations + review guidance + practice tasks + adaptive follow-up question",
          "Recommendation-module results should be the focus here: after recommendation, Not Competent/Beginner decreased and Intermediate/Expert increased across all five concepts (Fig. 7); pre/post gains were significant for all concepts (p < 0.0001), with mean gains of +22.47, +18.50, +15.97, +13.21, and +1.28 depending on the concept; learner survey showed strongest ratings for relevance and structure of recommendations (>3.3/5) and weakest ratings for personalization to individual mistakes/needs (<3.0/5)",
          "Best framed as a remedial intervention recommender rather than a classical item recommender. Strong point: the paper evaluates the effect of recommendations directly with pre/post learner improvement and user perception, not only underlying model performance",
          "Single-institution study; recommendation quality is not compared against alternative recommender baselines; personalization was perceived as weaker than clarity/relevance; relies on human/instructor oversight and cross-verification"
        ]
      ],
      "index": 6
    },
    {
      "block_id": "3364750c-f3ba-8013-af08-e2c69a749ea2",
      "heading": "Summary Table REC",
      "rows": [
        [
          "Task",
          "Context",
          "Student Performance Definition",
          "Target",
          "Students",
          "Courses",
          "Data sources",
          "Features",
          "Flaw of Previous Models",
          "Novelty of Model",
          "Preprocessing Details",
          "Models",
          "Assessment Strategy",
          "Performance Metric: Best Model",
          "Comments",
          "Limitations"
        ],
        [
          "Classification",
          "Higher Education",
          "Whether learners have attained the required concept level",
          "Concept mastery probabilities; weak concepts are those below OBE target levels",
          "1,276 learners for KT training/testing dataset",
          "70+ courses in a 4-year CSE program",
          "Historical OBE exam data from AMPLE LMS; learner-question responses mapped to concepts; curriculum and course-outcome structure",
          "Learner interaction sequences, correctness, exercise/question content, concept mappings, OBE attainment labels",
          "Earlier KT approaches either rely mainly on response sequences or do not sufficiently incorporate exercise semantics/content. The paper argues this limits fine-grained concept-level gap detection for OBE-aligned personalization",
          "Uses Exercise-Aware Knowledge Tracing (EKT) to combine learner response history with semantic content of exercises, then uses predicted concept mastery to identify weak concepts for personalized follow-up",
          "Curriculum PDFs converted to text and aligned to concepts; learner-question attainment mapped to concept-level outcomes; 75/25 train-test split; 12 epochs; embedding dimension 100; LSTM hidden size 100; dropout 0.3; Adam optimizer 0.001; batch size 32; binary cross-entropy loss",
          "DKT, DKVMN, EKT, AKT, SimpleKT",
          "Holdout Method",
          "{AUC: 0.9334 - EKT, RMSE: 0.1828 - EKT}",
          "Good fit for KT table because KT is not peripheral here: it is the mechanism used to estimate concept mastery and trigger downstream intervention. Figures 4–6 show model comparison, learner knowledge-state evolution, and concept-wise mastery visualization",
          "Single-institution OBE dataset; results tied to one engineering program; only holdout evaluation reported; paper emphasizes downstream application more than deep ablation of the KT component"
        ]
      ],
      "index": 8
    }
  ],
